@node not01 "FEATURES OF AMOZILLAX"

@{U}FEATURES OF @{B}AMOZILLAX@{UB}@{UU}

@{I}FOR INMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

@{B}aMozillaX @{UB} intends  to  offer  you  the  most  powerful browser available on any
platform.  We have implemented most features available in @{B}Mozilla @{UB}(except skins)
and added many, many more features that should make it your number 1 choice.

Full Features List:

  * @{I}Layout@{UI}
        @{B}HTML4.0 @{UB}Compliant "@{B}Gecko@{UB}" Layout Engine
          * Complete support except for bidirectional text layout, which is only
            used in Hebrew and Arabic
          * Style Sheets
          * @{B}CSS 1 @{UB}- complete support
          * @{B}CSS 2 @{UB}- partial support
          * @{B}DOM 1@{UB}
          * @{B}XML 1.0@{UB}
          * @{B}JavaScript 1.5 @{UB}(inc. @{B}ECMAScript @{UB}compliance)
          * @{B}PNG@{UB}, @{B}JPEG@{UB}, @{B}GIF@{UB}, @{B}XBM@{UB}, @{B}IFF@{UB}

  * @{I}@{B}Java@{UB}@{UI}
        Full @{B}Java @{UB}(Optional)
          * @{B}Java @{UB}Engine supplied by a well known @{B}Amiga @{UB}software company
          * @{B}Netscape Grendel Java @{UB}Mail Client
          * @{B}aMozillaIRC Java @{UB}IRC Client

  * @{I}Plugin@{UI}
      * Plugin API
          * Propriatary and @{B}Arexx @{UB}plugin API`s
      * Plugins Included
          * Propriatary
              * @{B}Shockwave@{UB}
              * @{B}Real Audio@{UB}
          * @{B}Arexx @{UB}Plugins
              * There will be a number of @{B}Arexx @{UB}plugins released with @{B}aMozillaX@{UB}

  * @{I}Network@{UI}
        Networking dealt with by 'network.library'
          * Intelligent Downloading
          * Downloads  are dealt with by an external program that is not reliant
            on   @{B}aMozillaX @{UB}  running.   This   download   tool  will  also  have
            'SilentDownload' technology, which maximises Bandwidth efficiency by
            only downloading when network.library is idle. (Optional)
          * @{B}HTTP1.1@{UB}, @{B}FTP@{UB}, @{B}Gopher@{UB}
          * @{B}SSL @{UB}128 bit Encryption

  * @{I}Other Features@{UI}
      * URL Completion (Optional)
      * Remote Access mode - allow someone else to control your browser, using a
        password protected direct link
      * Assign websites to Hotkeys
      * TV  Remote  Control,  @{B}Microsoft Intellimouse @{UB}(and similar), Input Device
        support
      * Inbuilt web server (Optional)
      * Magnifying Glass
      * @{B}AOL @{UB}Instant Messenger
      * Full control of GUI - drag and drop toolbars
      * Multiple  Selection  of  Links - pre-select the links you wish to visit,
        and @{B}aMozillaX @{UB}will load them all and you can switch straight to the next
        link

@{B}aMozillaX @{UB} beta  will be released in early May. A full version of @{B}aMozillaX @{UB}will
be  released  at  the  @{B}World  Of  Amiga @{UB} show  1999.  @{B}aMozillaX @{UB}will be free and
unrestricted.

@{B}aMozillaX @{UB}will come in @{B}030@{UB}, @{B}040@{UB}, @{B}060 @{UB}pre-compiled binaries. Image libraries will
have  @{B}PPC @{UB} enhancement.  A  @{B}PPC @{UB}native version is expected in August. The source
code  will  be  made  available  and  a constant versioning system (CVS) will be
established.

@{B}aMozillaX @{UB} will be working with other developers in order to integrate @{B}aMozillaX@{UB}
technology into a range of other @{B}Amiga @{UB}products.

