@node not02 "SPACE STATION 3000 DEMO RELEASED"

@{U}@{B}SPACE STATION 3000 @{UB}DEMO RELEASED@{UU}

The  eargely  awaited  demo  version of the upcoming game @{B}Space Station 3000 @{UB}has
been finally released. The demo is avalaible from the @{B}Digital Images @{UB}website.

This  demo  shows how the @{B}Genetic Species @{UB}engine shall be used for @{B}Space Station
3000@{UB}.  This  level  is  taken  from  one  of the enemy bases. Your mission is to
destroy all robots aboard the base. You can quit the demo by pressing Esc.

Unfortunately, the strategy part of the game has not been included in this demo.
The download for this would be around 40Mb!

@{B}Space  Station  3000 @{UB}requires 1Mb Chip RAM, 8Mb Fast RAM, an @{B}020 @{UB}or better, 21Mb
HD space and either @{B}AGA @{UB}or gfx card.

You   can  pre-order  @{B}Space  Station  3000 @{UB} from  the  @{B}Blittersoft @{UB} homepage  at
@{B}www.blittersoft.com @{UB} for  £24.95.  You  can  also  telephone them on +44 (0)1908
261466

If  you  have  any  questions,  queries  or suggestions, you can contact @{B}Digital
Images @{UB}via e-mail at
  * @{I}info@digital-images.demon.co.uk@{UI}
You can also look at
  * @{B}www.digital-images.demon.co.uk@{UB}
for lots of information.
