@node not06 "SHOGO COMING TO THE AMIGA"

@{U}@{B}SHOGO @{UB}COMING TO THE @{B}AMIGA@{UB}@{UU}

OK,  for all those that are eager for new games, here's a press release from the
new company @{B}Hyperion@{UB}.

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

@{B}Hyperion @{UB} is  pleased to announce that it has (in close co-operation with @{I}Stuart
Walker @{UI}from @{B}Digital Images@{UB}) acquired the rights from @{B}Monolith @{UB}to port @{B}Shogo@{UB}, the
highly acclaimed @{B}PC @{UB}game, to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

@{B}Shogo @{UB}is a high-end 3D shooter with anime/manga (Japanese cartoons) elements and
is based on the @{B}LithTech @{UB}(tm) engine developed by @{B}Monolith @{UB}(@{B}www.lith.com@{UB}).

As part of the deal with @{B}Monolith@{UB}, @{B}Hyperion @{UB}will port the @{B}LithTech @{UB}engine, which
is the most advanced 3D game engine around, to the @{B}Amiga @{UB}for future licensing by
@{B}Monolith@{UB}.

@{B}Shogo @{UB}will require a @{B}PPC @{UB}equipped @{B}Amiga @{UB}(@{B}WarpOS@{UB}) and will take full advantage of
3D accelerators through @{B}Warp3D@{UB}.

No  release  date  has been set yet but it is likely this will be 3rd quarter of
1999.

The   @{B}Hyperion @{UB}  team  consists  of  @{I}Thomas @{UI} and  @{I}Hans-Joerg  Frieden @{UI} (@{B}Warp  3D@{UB}
co-authors),  @{I}Christian  Sauer @{UI} who  was  involved  with  various  projects like
@{B}Descent@{UB}, and others.

@{B}Hyperion @{UB} is  a  newly  founded  Belgian-German  software  company  dedicated to
bringing high-end @{B}PC @{UB}titles to @{B}PPC @{UB}equipped @{B}Amiga@{UB}s.

For  those that don't know @{B}Shogo@{UB}, it is some game similar in concept to @{B}Quake @{UB}or
@{B}Unreal@{UB}.  The  game  itself  has an Anime-Style background and is centered around
MCA's, or Mobile Combat Armours, which are some kind of @{B}BattleMech@{UB}'s.

