@node not33 "AMIGA MONTHLY ASKED QUESTIONS - MAY 1999"

@{U}@{B}AMIGA @{UB}MONTHLY ASKED QUESTIONS - MAY 1999@{UU}

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

  * @{I}When is @{B}3.5 @{UB}shipping? @{UI}
    For  the  questions  to  @{B}3.5 @{UB} please  visit  the  @{B}3.5 @{UB} Web Site directly at:
    @{B}www.amiga.com/amigaos35/index.html@{UB}

  * @{I}How are betas being selected for @{B}3.5 @{UB}? @{UI}
    Beta  testers  for  @{B}3.5 @{UB}are being selected directly by @{B}Haage & Partner@{UB}. Beta
    testers  will  be notified by @{B}Haage & Partner @{UB}once the selection process has
    been completed.

  * @{I}What is the shipping base configuration for @{B}3.5 @{UB}? @{UI}
    Again  please visit the @{B}3.5 @{UB}web site at: @{B}www.amiga.com/amigaos35/index.html@{UB},
    for all @{B}3.5 @{UB}questions.

  * @{I}When is the development system scheduled for shipment? @{UI}
    We  are targeting release of the development product during Q4 of this year.
    We are planning to release more details on the development system in July.

  * @{I}What is the system specification for the development system? @{UI}
    As we move closer to the Q4 ship date, we will be releasing more information
    about   the   complete   @{B}Amiga  Operating  Environment @{UB} and  the  supporting
    development system.

  * @{I}Which processor has been selected for the development system? @{UI}
    In  order  to  shorten our time to release, we expect to release the initial
    development  environment  on  the  @{B}X.86 @{UB}architecture. We will ensure that we
    have  all  the  development  tools, libraries, etc. necessary to explore and
    begin  development  on  the  new  @{B}Amiga@{UB}s.  Please note, that using @{B}X.86 @{UB}as a
    development  system  doesn't  mean that we have selected an @{B}x86 @{UB}architecture
    for the new @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

  * @{I}What development tools will be available for the development system? @{UI}
    @{B}C++ @{UB} and  @{B}Java @{UB} are  the  primary  languages, supporting a rich set of @{B}Amiga@{UB}
    objects. More specific details will be released in July.

  * @{I}Is @{B}Java2 @{UB}part of @{B}OS5 @{UB}? @{UI}
    Yes,   we  feel  that  @{B}Java2 @{UB} offers  significant  advantages  for  portable
    applications.

  * @{I}Will existing @{B}Amiga @{UB}dealers sell the development system ?@{UI}
    We  will  be  working  with  the @{B}Amiga @{UB}dealer channel to arrange for them to
    deliver the new @{B}Amiga @{UB}products.

  * @{I}Is the next generation @{B}Amiga @{UB}still scheduled to ship Christmas 1999? @{UI}
    Yes,  we are still targeting to ship by Q4 this year. We are working through
    the precise product launch plans, but plan to release the product globally.

  * @{I}Which processor has been selected for the next generation @{B}Amiga @{UB}? @{UI}
    The  final  decision  on the processor for the Next Generation @{B}Amiga @{UB}has not
    been  made. There are several under consideration, and we are continuing our
    process of evaluation and feature comparisons.

  * @{I}When will we begin seeing advertising for the next generation @{B}Amiga @{UB}? @{UI}
    We  do  not  expect  to  do any external advertising for the new @{B}Amiga @{UB}until
    there are products available through our distribution channels. We are still
    some  months  away  from  that  so  there  are  no  definitive plans for the
    advertising  program.  We  do intend to communicate product availability and
    other   company   activities  through  the  established  @{B}Amiga @{UB} channels  of
    communication prior to general market communications.

  * @{I}Will @{B}Amiga @{UB}have a presence at @{B}Comdex @{UB}this year? @{UI}
    We  are planning activities at the several of the @{B}Amiga @{UB}and general industry
    events.  The  successful  participation  in  a  trade  show like Fall @{B}Comdex@{UB}
    involves a lot of advance planning and having the right message at the right
    time  in  order to gain visibility above the noise level at that show. As we
    get closer to @{B}Comdex@{UB}, we will disclose our plans for participation.

  * @{I}How do we become beta testers to the next generation @{B}Amiga @{UB}? @{UI}
    The  Beta  program for the next generation product has not been defined yet.
    We expect to make this information available by late summer.
