@node not49 "NETINFO-II 2.0 RELEASED"

@{U}@{B}NETINFO-II 2.0 @{UB}RELEASED@{UU}

@{B}NetInfo   II @{UB} is  a  network  information  viewer  utility.  It  integrates  the
functionality  of  the  well known standalone TRACEROUTE, PING, WHOIS and FINGER
programs into a seamless GUI application.

How to obtain
  * netinfo_20.lha (241831 Bytes)
  * netinfo_20.lzx (184283 Bytes)

FTP:
  * @{B}ftp.vapor.com@{UB}, /pub/netinfo/
  * @{B}ftp.us.vapor.com@{UB}, /pub/netinfo/

WWW:
  * @{B}www.vapor.com@{UB}
  * @{B}vapor.ukonline.co.uk@{UB}
  * @{B}vapor.meanmachine.ch@{UB}

E-MAIL:
  * Mail to @{I}<fileserv@vapor.com>@{UI}, put "SEND NETINFO" in the body.

AmiNet:
  * /pub/aminet/comm/tcp/netinfo.lha (within the next few days)

@{I}Features:@{UI}
  * "quick  traceroute"  Sends  a  series of packet in quick succession to get a
    route overview very fast, then does accurate timings for the individual hops
  * graphical display of hop min/last/max timings
  * integrated  smart  WHOIS  function:  double-click  on  a IP, Host or Network
    column  to  automatically  receive  WHOIS  information for the given object.
    @{B}NetInfo @{UB}determines the WHOIS host to query.
  * automatically retrieves WHOIS network information for hosts
  * automatically scans destination host for Web (HTTP) and FTP server versions
  * history for all queried hosts
  * integrated FINGER client
  * integrated "classical" WHOIS client with on-disk cache

NetInfo is © 1997-99 @{I}Oliver Wagner @{UI}@{I}<owagner@vapor.com>@{UI}, All Rights Reserved.

@{B}NetInfo @{UB} works  with  @{B}Genesis@{UB},  @{B}Miami @{UB} and  @{B}AmiTCP@{UB}. "socket.library"based TCP/IP
stacks  (as225r2 etc.) are not supported, and the traceroute functionality won't
work with SOCKS (whois and finger will, though).

@{B}NetInfo @{UB} uses  @{B}MUI 3.8 @{UB}and the "NList" list classes by @{I}Gilles Masson@{UI}. "NList" is
available from @{B}AmiNet @{UB}or from @{B}ftp.vapor.com@{UB}, in the "/pub/3rdparty/" directory.
